text: Garrison Tubbs (Born February 17, 2002) is an American soccer player who plays for the Wake Forest Demon Deacons in the NCAA Division I. == Club career == On July 27, 2019, Tubbs appeared for Atlanta United 2, the USL Championship affiliate of Atlanta United, as a 71st-minute substitute in a 4-2 loss to North Carolina FC. == References == ==External links== * Category:2002 births Category:Living people Category:American soccer players Category:Association football defenders Category:Atlanta United 2 players Category:Soccer players from Florida Category:USL Championship players Category:Sportspeople from Jacksonville, Florida Category:Wake Forest Demon Deacons men's soccer players
